The families of serial killer Siyamcela Sombambela's victims hope his sentencing will lead to closure. eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. #DStv403 WOLSELEY - Closure is within reach for the families of three women who lost their lives to a serial killer in Wolseley. Siyamcela Sombambela is being sentenced on Friday for the murders in 2020. He buried all his victims in the same spot. Sombambela was caught by neighbourhood watch members in Pine Valley in October 2020, dragging Bernadine Frans’ body to a make-shift burial site. He will be sentenced in the Worcester magistrate’s court. * eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports.